Box: Passage
Difficulty: Medium
OS: Linux

Recon:
- nmap -sC -sV -p- <IP>
- Found HTTP on port 80, SSH on 22
- Discovered CMS Made Simple via web content

Exploitation:
- CMS Made Simple vulnerable to SQLi (public exploit available)
- Extracted creds from database
- Used creds to log in via SSH

Privilege Escalation:
- Enumerated sudo -l, found user allowed to run /usr/bin/perl as root
- Escalated with perl -e 'exec "/bin/sh";'

Mitigations:
- Patch CMS, sanitize queries
- Enforce least privilege on sudo
- Segregate web creds from system creds
